SERVER TYPE A — ASSEMBLY DOCUMENTATION
Model: AI Compute Server – Type A
Purpose: High-performance training and inference for AI workloads.
1. SERVER TYPE A – TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS
1.1 Form Factor
4U Rack-mount chassis (supports multiple GPUs and high airflow)
1.2 CPU & Memory
Dual Intel Xeon Scalable Processors (or AMD EPYC equivalent)
16 DIMM slots total
Max capacity: 1 TB DDR4/DDR5 ECC Registered RAM
1.3 GPUs
4 × NVIDIA A100 / H100 PCIe GPUs
Passive cooling design (relies on chassis airflow)
1.4 Storage
2 × NVMe SSD (2TB each) – OS + logs
4 × SATA/SAS SSD/HDD – Data storage
1.5 Power Supply
Dual 2000W redundant PSUs
1.6 Networking
Dual 25GbE / 40GbE NIC
Optional InfiniBand HDR for multi-GPU clusters
1.7 Other Components
GPU power cables
CPU heatsinks
PCIe riser cards
Cooling fans (hot-swappable trays)
Rail kit for rack installation
2. SAFETY & PREPARATION
2.1 Personal Safety
Wear ESD wrist strap and connect to ground.
No metal jewelry during assembly.
2.2 Workspace Requirements
Clean, well-lit table
Antistatic mat
All components laid out and checked against BOM (Bill of Materials)
2.3 Tools Required
Phillips screwdriver (#2)
Torque screwdriver (optional for CPU heatsink)
Flashlight
Thermal paste (if heatsinks don’t come pre-applied)
3. STEP-BY-STEP ASSEMBLY PROCESS (TYPE A SERVER)
STEP 1 — UNBOX & PRE-CHECK
Place chassis on the antistatic mat.
Remove the top cover and keep screws safely aside.
Perform a visual inspection:- No bent pins- No loose components- All screws included
Verify you have all sub-components:- CPU (2)- RAM (16 sticks or as required)- GPUs (4)- NVMe SSDs- PCIe risers- Fan modules- Power supplies
STEP 2 — INSTALL THE CPUs
2.1 Open CPU Sockets
Lift the retention levers.
Open the protective cover.
2.2 Handle the CPU
Hold CPU by the edges only.
Never touch the gold contacts or pins.
2.3 Align & Install
Match the triangle marker on the CPU with marker on the socket.
Gently lower it—do not slide the CPU.
Close the socket latch and lock both levers.
Common Mistake to Avoid:
Placing the CPU backward. Always check alignment twice.
STEP 3 — INSTALL CPU HEATSINKS
If thermal paste is not pre-applied, put a pea-sized dot on the CPU.
Align the heatsink screws with mounting posts.
Tighten in a cross pattern.
Make sure it feels firm; do not overtighten.
STEP 4 — INSTALL MEMORY (RAM)
Check the memory population guide.
Open side latches of the DIMM slots.
Insert each RAM stick firmly until both latches click.
Ensure they are fully seated.
Tip:
Install RAM in the blue-colored slots first.
STEP 5 — INSTALL NVMe SSDs (OS DRIVES)
Locate the M.2 or NVMe PCIe slots.
Insert drive at slight angle.
Push down and screw into place.
If carriers are used, insert into front bays.
STEP 6 — INSTALL DATA DRIVES
Open drive trays.
Place SSD/HDD inside.
Secure with 4 screws.
Slide tray in until latch clicks.
STEP 7 — INSTALL PCIe RISER MODULES
Insert each riser into its motherboard slot.
Tighten screws.
Ensure proper alignment.
STEP 8 — INSTALL NVIDIA GPUs
8.1 Prepare Area
Place GPUs on antistatic mat.
Inspect PCIe contacts.
8.2 Insert Into Riser
Hold GPU with two hands.
Insert straight into riser.
Align bracket and tighten screw.
8.3 Connect Power Cables
Connect 8-pin or 12-pin connectors.
Ensure they click in firmly.
STEP 9 — INSTALL NETWORK CARDS
Insert NIC/InfiniBand card.
Tighten bracket screw.
STEP 10 — INSTALL FAN MODULES
Slide each module into slot until it clicks.
Confirm airflow direction.
STEP 11 — INSTALL POWER SUPPLIES
Slide into bay until it clicks.
Install two PSUs.
STEP 12 — CABLE MANAGEMENT
Use velcro straps.
Ensure no cable touches fans.
Keep GPU power cables tidy.
STEP 13 — FIRST POWER-ON TEST
Checklist:- Fans installed- Power cables connected- Heatsinks tightened- RAM seated
Procedure:
Connect PSUs.
Press power button.
Indicators:- Fans spin strongly- Status LEDs green- One beep = good
STEP 14 — MOUNT SERVER ON RACK
Install rail kit.
Attach rails to rack and chassis.
Slide server in with two people.
Tighten front thumbscrews.
STEP 15 — CONNECT NETWORKS & POWER
Connect PSUs to redundant PDUs.
Connect NICs, InfiniBand, BMC/IPMI cable.
STEP 16 — FINAL BOOT & CONFIGURATION
Power on in rack.
Access IPMI/BMC.
Configure BIOS settings.
Install OS.
Install NVIDIA drivers + CUDA.
Run nvidia-smi to validate GPUs.
FINAL VERIFICATION CHECKLIST
 System boots to OS
 All 4 GPUs visible
 All RAM detected
 All drives detected
 All fans operational
 BMC reachable
 NIC bandwidth test passes
